org.apache.paimon.flink.action.cdc.format.canal

Class CanalRecordParser

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.paimon.flink.action.cdc.format.RecordParser
      • org.apache.paimon.flink.action.cdc.format.canal.CanalRecordParser
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, org.apache.flink.api.common.functions.FlatMapFunction<CdcSourceRecord,RichCdcMultiplexRecord>, org.apache.flink.api.common.functions.Function

    public class CanalRecordParser
extends RecordParser
    The CanalRecordParser class is responsible for parsing records from the Canal-JSON format. Canal is a database binlog multi-platform consumer, which is used to synchronize data across databases. This parser extracts relevant information from the Canal-JSON format and transforms it into a list of RichCdcMultiplexRecord objects, which represent the changes captured in the database.

    The class handles different types of database operations such as INSERT, UPDATE, and DELETE, and generates corresponding RichCdcMultiplexRecord objects for each operation.

    Additionally, the parser supports schema extraction, which can be used to understand the structure of the incoming data and its corresponding field types.
